.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F4ABFE4AE9104B63BC4E99579D0925D5" pageId="7" pageNumber="126">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1C51E3D9005C15736A50E35C1775D66C" pageId="7" pageNumber="126" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C546E618A77BD836C6D43A519239E94D" pageId="7" pageNumber="126">Etymology,</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E9331A20219E2B26AA844A99CE40A0DE" pageId="7" pageNumber="126">From Latin spatulata = spatulated, referring to the shape of the gonocoxite apex.</paragraph>
